
Implementation Specification - Volume 1

Repository & Configuration Architecture

Version: 1.0

Status: Approved Baseline

---

1. Purpose

This document defines the repository structure, configuration hierarchy, directory contracts, naming standards, variable contracts, and manifest contracts for the Regression Automation Framework.

All implementation artifacts shall conform to this specification.

---

2. Repository Structure

The repository shall be organized as follows:

regression-automation-framework/

├── playbooks/
│
├── roles/
│
├── group_vars/
│
├── manifests/
│
├── schemas/
│
├── scripts/
│
├── templates/
│
├── reports/
│
├── docs/
│
├── tests/
│
└── README.md

---

3. Playbook Structure

playbooks/

├── validate_manifest.yml
├── validate_runtime_host.yml
├── execute_parallel.yml
├── execute_sequential.yml
├── resume_execution.yml
├── generate_reports.yml
└── notify.yml

Rules:

- One business capability per playbook
- Playbooks orchestrate roles
- Business logic shall not reside in playbooks
- Playbooks only coordinate execution

---

4. Role Structure

roles/

├── manifest_validation/
├── runtime_host_validation/
├── runtime_user_validation/
├── artifact_download/
├── cleanup/
├── precheck/
├── deploy/
├── sanity/
├── execute/
├── validate/
├── reporting/
├── notification/
├── checkpoint/
└── resume/

Every role shall contain:

role_name/

├── defaults/
│   └── main.yml
│
├── tasks/
│   └── main.yml
│
├── handlers/
│   └── main.yml
│
├── vars/
│   └── main.yml
│
├── templates/
│
└── README.md

---

5. Environment Configuration Hierarchy

Configuration shall be resolved in the following order:

all.yml
    ↓
platform.yml
    ↓
environment.yml
    ↓
manifest values

Later values override earlier values.

---

6. Configuration Files

group_vars/

├── all.yml
├── platform.yml
├── dev.yml
├── qa.yml
├── uat.yml
└── prod.yml

---

7. all.yml Contract

Contains framework defaults.

Example:

max_parallel_artifacts: 5

max_parallel_jobs_per_artifact: 2

default_artifact_timeout_minutes: 120

report_retention_days: 30

checkpoint_retention_days: 15

artifact_download_retry_count: 3

artifact_download_retry_delay_seconds: 30

notify_on_failure: true

notify_on_completion: true

Rules:

- No environment-specific values
- No credentials
- No host names

---

8. platform.yml Contract

Contains organization-wide values.

Example:

artifactory_base_url: https://artifactory.company.com

smtp_host: smtp.company.com

smtp_port: 25

workspace_root: /apps/regression/workspace

report_root: /apps/regression/reports

checkpoint_root: /apps/regression/checkpoints

log_root: /apps/regression/logs

Rules:

- Shared across all environments
- No environment-specific values

---

9. Environment Configuration Contract

Example: qa.yml

environment_name: QA

artifactory_repo: regression-qa

allowed_runtime_users:
  - svc_regression
  - qa_user

notification_recipients:
  - qa-team@company.com

max_concurrent_runs: 2

artifact_timeout_minutes: 180

Rules:

- Only environment-specific values
- No runtime values
- No host names

---

10. Runtime Manifest Location

User manifests shall reside in:

manifests/

Example:

manifests/run_001.json

---

11. Manifest Contract

Manifest is the primary runtime input.

Example:

{
  "runId": "RUN_001",
  "environment": "QA",
  "targetHost": "qa-host-01",
  "executionMode": "PARALLEL",
  "artifacts": []
}

Rules:

- Manifest drives execution
- Manifest overrides configuration where allowed
- Manifest validated before execution

---

12. Mandatory Manifest Fields

{
  "runId": "",
  "environment": "",
  "targetHost": "",
  "executionMode": "",
  "artifacts": []
}

Required:

runId
environment
targetHost
executionMode
artifacts

---

13. Artifact Definition Contract

Every artifact must contain:

{
  "artifactId": "",
  "artifactName": "",
  "artifactType": "",
  "deploymentRequired": true,
  "execution": {}
}

---

14. Workspace Directory Contract

Execution workspace:

/apps/regression/workspace/<run_id>

Example:

/apps/regression/workspace/RUN_001

---

15. Artifact Workspace Contract

Each artifact receives dedicated workspace.

Example:

/apps/regression/workspace/RUN_001/payment-service

/apps/regression/workspace/RUN_001/billing-service

Rules:

- No sharing between artifacts
- Required for parallel execution

---

16. Report Directory Contract

Execution reports:

/apps/regression/reports/<run_id>

Example:

/apps/regression/reports/RUN_001

---

17. Checkpoint Directory Contract

Checkpoint storage:

/apps/regression/checkpoints/<run_id>

Example:

/apps/regression/checkpoints/RUN_001

---

18. Naming Standards

Variables

Use snake_case.

Example:

artifact_timeout_minutes

Invalid:

artifactTimeoutMinutes

---

Roles

Use lowercase.

Example:

manifest_validation
runtime_host_validation

---

Playbooks

Use lowercase.

Example:

execute_parallel.yml

---

19. Logging Contract

Every role shall log:

START
END
FAILURE

Format:

[TIMESTAMP]
[RUN_ID]
[ARTIFACT]
[ROLE]
[MESSAGE]

Example:

2025-05-18T10:15:00Z
RUN_001
payment-service
deploy
Deployment completed

---

20. Configuration Anti-Patterns

The following shall NOT be stored in configuration files:

runId
targetHost
executionMode
resumeRunId
selectedArtifacts

These belong in runtime manifests.

---

21. Definition of Done

Volume 1 is considered implemented when:

✓ Repository structure created

✓ Role skeletons created

✓ Playbook skeletons created

✓ Configuration hierarchy implemented

✓ Manifest location established

✓ Variable loading implemented

✓ Environment resolution implemented

✓ Logging standard implemented

✓ Directory contracts enforced
Implementation Specification - Volume 2

Execution Framework & Role Contracts

Version: 1.0

Status: Approved Baseline

---

1. Purpose

This document defines the execution framework, role contracts, playbook orchestration, execution lifecycle, parallel execution model, timeout framework, and role interaction contracts.

This document is the primary implementation guide for coding agents.

---

2. Execution Modes

Supported execution modes:

SEQUENTIAL
PARALLEL
RESUME

---

3. Artifact Lifecycle

Every artifact shall execute the following lifecycle:

cleanup
  ↓
precheck
  ↓
deploy
  ↓
sanity
  ↓
execute
  ↓
validate
  ↓
housekeeping

Rules:

- Order is mandatory
- Failure stops lifecycle for that artifact
- In PARALLEL mode, failure of one artifact does not stop others
- Status must be recorded after every phase

---

4. Standard Role Interface

Every role shall expose the following output contract.

role_result:
  status: SUCCESS|FAILED|SKIPPED|TIMEOUT
  phase: cleanup
  start_time:
  end_time:
  duration_seconds:
  error_message:

---

5. Execution Context Contract

Every role shall receive:

run_id:
artifact_id:
artifact_name:
environment:
target_host:
execution_mode:
artifact_workspace:
artifact_report_directory:
artifact_checkpoint_directory:

---

6. Cleanup Role

Role:

roles/cleanup

Purpose:

Remove previous execution artifacts.

Inputs:

artifact_workspace:

Tasks:

1. Verify workspace exists
2. Remove temporary files
3. Remove previous outputs
4. Preserve checkpoint files

Outputs:

cleanup_result:
  status:

Failure Conditions:

Workspace inaccessible
Permission denied

---

7. Precheck Role

Role:

roles/precheck

Purpose:

Validate execution prerequisites.

Checks:

Disk space
Workspace availability
Artifact source accessibility
Required runtime availability

Outputs:

precheck_result:
  status:
  failed_checks:

Failure:

Any mandatory prerequisite fails.

---

8. Artifact Download Role

Role:

roles/artifact_download

Purpose:

Retrieve deployment package.

Inputs:

artifact_source_url:
download_directory:

Tasks:

1. Validate URL
2. Download artifact
3. Verify artifact exists
4. Capture checksum if available

Output:

download_result:
  status:
  local_path:

---

9. Deploy Role

Role:

roles/deploy

Purpose:

Deploy artifact to execution workspace.

Inputs:

artifact_path:
deployment_directory:

Tasks:

1. Create deployment directory
2. Backup existing deployment (optional)
3. Deploy artifact
4. Verify deployment

Output:

deploy_result:
  status:

---

10. Sanity Role

Role:

roles/sanity

Purpose:

Validate successful deployment.

Checks:

Required files exist
Permissions valid
Executable files accessible

Output:

sanity_result:
  status:

---

11. Execute Role

Role:

roles/execute

Purpose:

Execute artifact workload.

Inputs:

command:
working_directory:
timeout_minutes:
environment_variables:

Tasks:

1. Launch process
2. Monitor process
3. Capture exit code
4. Capture stdout
5. Capture stderr
6. Record execution duration

Output:

execution_result:
  status:
  exit_code:
  duration_seconds:
  stdout_file:
  stderr_file:

---

12. Validation Role

Role:

roles/validate

Purpose:

Determine regression outcome.

Inputs:

comparison_script:
expected_output_location:
actual_output_location:

Tasks:

1. Execute validation logic
2. Compare outputs
3. Generate validation summary

Output:

validation_result:
  status:
  differences_found:
  difference_count:

---

13. Housekeeping Role

Role:

roles/housekeeping

Purpose:

Archive execution artifacts.

Tasks:

1. Compress temporary outputs
2. Move artifacts to archive
3. Remove transient files

Output:

housekeeping_result:
  status:

---

14. Reporting Role

Role:

roles/reporting

Purpose:

Generate artifact reports.

Generates:

artifact_result.json
validation_result.json

Output Location:

reports/<run_id>/<artifact_name>

---

15. Notification Role

Role:

roles/notification

Purpose:

Generate notifications.

Notification Types:

FAILURE
COMPLETION
SUMMARY

Transport:

AWX Native Notifications

---

16. Checkpoint Role

Role:

roles/checkpoint

Purpose:

Persist execution state.

Checkpoint Events:

STARTED
COMPLETED
FAILED
SKIPPED

Generated Files:

artifact_name.started
artifact_name.completed
artifact_name.failed
artifact_name.skipped

---

17. Parallel Execution Framework

Playbook:

playbooks/execute_parallel.yml

Objective:

Execute multiple artifact pipelines concurrently.

---

18. Parallel Execution Contract

Maximum:

max_parallel_artifacts: 5

Execution Model:

Artifact A Pipeline
Artifact B Pipeline
Artifact C Pipeline
Artifact D Pipeline
Artifact E Pipeline

Each artifact owns:

workspace
report directory
checkpoint directory

No shared artifact resources allowed.

---

19. Parallel Failure Isolation

Failure of:

Artifact A

must not stop:

Artifact B
Artifact C
Artifact D

Summary report aggregates final status.

---

20. Sequential Execution Framework

Playbook:

playbooks/execute_sequential.yml

Execution Model:

Artifact A
  ↓
Artifact B
  ↓
Artifact C

Rules:

- Next artifact starts only after previous artifact completes
- No approval nodes in Phase 1

---

21. Timeout Framework

Timeout Scope:

Artifact Level

Implementation:

artifact_timeout_minutes:

Behavior:

1. Detect timeout
2. Terminate process
3. Mark artifact TIMEOUT
4. Trigger notification
5. Update checkpoint

---

22. Status Model

Allowed Status Values:

PENDING
RUNNING
SUCCESS
FAILED
TIMEOUT
SKIPPED

No additional status values allowed.

---

23. Failure Classification

Framework shall classify:

CONFIGURATION_FAILURE
PRECHECK_FAILURE
DOWNLOAD_FAILURE
DEPLOYMENT_FAILURE
SANITY_FAILURE
EXECUTION_FAILURE
VALIDATION_FAILURE
TIMEOUT_FAILURE

---

24. Artifact Pipeline Contract

Artifact pipeline result:

{
  "artifactName": "",
  "status": "",
  "failureType": "",
  "startTime": "",
  "endTime": "",
  "durationSeconds": 0
}

---

25. Playbook Responsibilities

validate_manifest.yml

Validate execution manifest

validate_runtime_host.yml

Validate target host

execute_parallel.yml

Run parallel artifact pipelines

execute_sequential.yml

Run sequential artifact pipelines

resume_execution.yml

Resume failed execution

generate_reports.yml

Aggregate reports

notify.yml

Generate notifications

---

26. Coding Rules

Roles SHALL:

Be idempotent
Return structured outputs
Not call AWX APIs directly
Not contain hardcoded paths
Not contain hardcoded credentials

Playbooks SHALL:

Only orchestrate roles
Contain minimal business logic

---

27. Definition of Done

Volume 2 is complete when:

✓ All roles created

✓ Role contracts implemented

✓ Artifact lifecycle implemented

✓ Parallel execution implemented

✓ Sequential execution implemented

✓ Timeout framework implemented

✓ Failure classification implemented

✓ Reporting hooks integrated

✓ Checkpoint hooks integrated

