---

9. Overall Status Rules

Overall status calculation:

IF any artifact TIMEOUT
    OVERALL = FAILED

ELSE IF any artifact FAILED
    OVERALL = FAILED

ELSE
    OVERALL = SUCCESS

---

10. Report Aggregation Algorithm

Input:

artifact_result.json
validation_result.json

Algorithm:

1. Read all artifact reports
2. Read all validation reports
3. Calculate counts
4. Build execution_summary.json
5. Publish reports
6. Trigger notifications

---

11. Checkpoint Architecture

Checkpoint system supports:

Execution Recovery
Resume Workflow
Execution Audit

Checkpoint system is filesystem based.

No database dependency.

---

12. Checkpoint Directory Structure

checkpoints/

└── <run_id>/

    ├── run.properties

    ├── payment-service.completed

    ├── billing-service.failed

    └── settlement-service.pending

---

13. run.properties Contract

File:

run.properties

Example:

runId=RUN_001
environment=QA
targetHost=qa-host-01
executionMode=PARALLEL
startTime=2025-05-18T10:00:00Z

---

14. Artifact Marker File Contract

Allowed files:

artifact.started
artifact.completed
artifact.failed
artifact.skipped
artifact.timeout

Examples:

payment-service.completed
billing-service.failed

Only one terminal marker may exist.

---

15. Marker File Content

File contents:

artifactName=payment-service
status=COMPLETED
timestamp=2025-05-18T10:30:00Z

---

16. Checkpoint State Machine

PENDING
  ↓

STARTED
  ↓

COMPLETED
FAILED
TIMEOUT
SKIPPED

Terminal states:

COMPLETED
FAILED
TIMEOUT
SKIPPED

---

17. Resume Architecture

Phase 1 supports:

Artifact Boundary Resume

Phase-level resume is not supported.

---

18. Resume Rules

Resume is allowed only when:

Run previously failed
Checkpoint exists
Original host available

---

19. Host Validation Rules

Resume host must equal:

targetHost

stored in:

run.properties

Validation:

requested_host == checkpoint_host

If false:

Resume Rejected

---

20. Resume Algorithm

Input:

runId
targetHost

Algorithm:

1. Load run.properties

2. Validate host

3. Locate artifacts

4. Skip COMPLETED

5. Skip SKIPPED

6. Restart FAILED

7. Restart TIMEOUT

8. Continue execution

---

21. Example Resume

Checkpoint:

payment-service.completed
billing-service.failed
settlement-service.pending

Resume behavior:

Skip payment-service

Restart billing-service

Execute settlement-service

---

22. Parallel Execution Checkpoint Rules

Each artifact owns independent checkpoint files.

Example:

payment-service.completed
billing-service.failed
settlement-service.completed

Artifacts must never modify each other's checkpoint files.

---

